            "answer_text": "Different companies has different preferences, some choose by age, talent or experience. But they all have to have one thing in common: and that\u2019s leadership skills. Being able to lead a group and having the member\u2019s respect is important, so it\u2019s only natural the leader would be one of the elder members seeing as how in Korean culture, age is highly respected. Communication: Leaders also need to be able to communicate and lead the team, they\u2019re usually the ones to introduce their group on tv/radioshows etc so have to have good public speaking skills. Being proficient in different languages is also seen as a bonus for leaders, especially english, japanese or chinese. Skills: Being able to produce/write/make music for the team is also a leader quality. Leaders are usually either a main vocalist or rapper in order to be able to create music for the group. (other members also produce etc\u2026 but someone with these skills are more likely to be chosen over someone without) Taking this all into account, it\u2019s then the company\u2019s job to make a decision, usually taking into consideration the member\u2019s opinions and feelings on who they think could lead their group. ",
